<P><FONT size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the second quarter of 2000, we sold the <I>Rid</I> line of lice-control
products to Bayer Corporation. In the fourth quarter of 1999, we sold the <I>Bain
de Soleil</I> suncare product line to Schering-Plough HealthCare Products, Inc.
</FONT>
<P><FONT size="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CHC can extend the life of some of our prescription medications by
converting them to OTC medications. For example, an OTC formulation of <I>Diflucan</I>,
known as <I>Diflucan One</I>, is sold in the U.K. as a treatment for vaginal
candidiasis. Similarly, <I>Zyrtec</I> is sold as an OTC product in certain markets
outside the U.S. under the brand name <I>Reactine</I>. As market conditions permit, and
when we have necessary approval from drug regulatory authorities, we plan to
pursue similar launches for other products.
</FONT>
<P><FONT size="2"><I>Confectionery Products</I>
